        "title": "refactor(skills): trim bundled starter set",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- reduce the core-bundled starter set from 57 skill directories to 14:\n  `clawhub`, `diagram-maker`, `gifgrep`, `gog`, `healthcheck`, `mcporter`,\n  `model-usage`, `node-connect`, `peekaboo`, `skill-creator`, `songsee`,\n  `spotify-player`, `summarize`, and `weather`\n- move five owner-specific skills into their plugins and declare those plugin\n  skill surfaces: Canvas, Discord, Slack, voice-call, and WhatsApp (`wacli`)\n- prepare `2026.6.8-1` correction releases for the external Discord, Slack,\n  voice-call, and WhatsApp plugins so their owner skills can publish to npm and\n  ClawHub immediately after this PR merges\n- publish Sherpa ONNX TTS as the official external ClawHub-only plugin\n  `@openclaw/sherpa-onnx-tts`, register its trusted official catalog entry, and\n  support bare-ID install resolution for ClawHub-only official plugins\n- remove 37 optional skills from core, clean up the retained ClawHub skill to\n  use native `openclaw skills` discovery/install commands, and update affected\n  docs, generated plugin inventory, packaging, and obsolete tests\n\nPlugin-owned skills are visible when their owning plugin is active. Canvas\ncontinues to ship bundled with core. Discord, Slack, voice-call, and WhatsApp\nare external opt-in plugins, so their skill moves are paired with unpublished\ncorrection versions for post-merge publication. Sherpa is not included in core\nor published to npm; users install it from ClawHub. Its skill automatically\ndownloads the macOS universal runtime and Piper model, with manual upstream\nasset setup documented for Linux and Windows.\n\nThe root `skills/` directory and bundled-skill loading/configuration remain in\nplace. There are no system-prompt changes.\n\nRemoved from core:\n\n`1password`, `apple-notes`, `apple-reminders`, `bear-notes`, `blogwatcher`,\n`blucli`, `camsnap`, `coding-agent`, `eightctl`, `gemini`, `gh-issues`,\n`github`, `goplaces`, `himalaya`, `imsg`, `meme-maker`, `nano-pdf`,\n`node-inspect-debugger`, `notion`, `obsidian`, `openai-whisper`,\n`openai-whisper-api`, `openhue`, `oracle`, `ordercli`, `python-debugpy`, `sag`,\n`session-logs`, `sonoscli`, `spike`, `taskflow`, `taskflow-inbox-triage`,\n`things-mac`, `tmux`, `trello`, `video-frames`, and `xurl`.\n\n## Verification\n\n- focused Vitest proof across official plugin catalog/install/update,\n  ClawHub/npm release packaging, Sherpa wrapper behavior, plugin-owned skill\n  loading, and bundled skill discovery\n- `git diff --check upstream/main...HEAD`\n- bundled/plugin inventory, release metadata, and Plugin Inspector checks\n- AWS Crabbox `run_5395957a7d5b`: `pnpm check:changed && pnpm build` passed\n- npm and ClawHub release planners identify exactly four unpublished,\n  trusted-publisher `2026.6.8-1` `latest` candidates: Discord, Slack,\n  voice-call, and WhatsApp\n- package dry-runs confirm the four external owner plugins contain\n  `skills/discord/SKILL.md`, `skills/slack/SKILL.md`,\n  `skills/voice-call/SKILL.md`, and `skills/wacli/SKILL.md`\n- official Sherpa ClawHub release dry-run from the exact pushed source:\n  6-file `bundle-plugin`, SHA-256\n  `836662372e8da34ea25e6d2beacb45ba3584fe2d0e5093669994b16ca0d21558`\n- published and live-inspected `@openclaw/sherpa-onnx-tts@2026.6.8`: official,\n  clean-scanned, source-linked, and configured with the OpenClaw release\n  workflow as trusted publisher\n- isolated live ClawHub install loaded the Sherpa plugin and exposed\n  `sherpa-onnx-tts` as eligible, model-visible, and non-bundled\n- real macOS wrapper proof generated a valid 22.05 kHz mono PCM WAV\n- fresh correction-release autoreview: no accepted/actionable findings\n",
